// CONTRACTS enforce
// EXPECT_STDOUT PROVEN_ELIDED_OK
// EXPECT_EXIT_CODE 0
//
// Plan 140 Ф.3 (D24 amend), acceptance F2: Z3/Trivial-PROVEN contracts are
// elided at codegen (zero-cost), even under default `--contracts=enforce`.
//
// `inc_nonneg` carries `requires x >= 0` and `ensures result >= 1`. With the
// given body (`x + 1`) the postcondition is statically PROVABLE from the
// precondition: x >= 0 ⟹ x + 1 >= 1. Both the TrivialBackend (linear-arith)
// and Z3 discharge this VC, so the VerificationPipeline records it in
// `proven_contracts`.
//
// Ф.3 wires that proven set from check_module into the codegen emitter on the
// BUILD path (test-build / nova build / bench). Therefore the generated `.c`
// must contain NO `nova_contract_violation` call for `inc_nonneg`'s ensures —
// it is elided. The companion check `inspect_elision.sh` asserts the `.c` has
// zero contract-violation calls for the proven ensures.
//
// This fixture is called with a value that SATISFIES the precondition (5), so
// even if the contract were (incorrectly) still checked, it would pass; the
// behavioural assertion is exit 0 + stdout. The STATIC assertion (proven ⟹
// elided) is verified by inspecting the emitted `.c`.

module plan140.t2_proven_elided

fn inc_nonneg(x int) -> int
    requires x >= 0
    ensures result >= 1
=> x + 1

fn main() Io -> () {
    ro y = inc_nonneg(5)
    if y == 6 {
        println("PROVEN_ELIDED_OK")
    } else {
        println("UNEXPECTED")
    }
}
